    "summary": "Expose endoint providing an unique OrderNumber/ReturnOrderNumber",
    "url": "https://richemont.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/93184",
    "description": "*1.Endpoint Definition:*\n\n   •A new HTTP GET request. REST endpoint must be implemented within the ce-order service.\n\n* The endpoint must accept a mandatory query parameter, type, to categorize the generated number.\n* Valid type values include, but are not limited to: orderNumber, ReturnOrderNumber.\n* The endpoint must be accessible via a query parameter like ?type=orderNumber.\n* The endpoint must be accessible via a path like /numbers/get.\n\n\n*2.Number Generation and Retrieval:*\n\n* Generate a new, unique alphanumeric identifier for the specified type.\n* The generated must be returned as a string in the response body.\n\n*3.Uniqueness Enforcement:*\n\n* ce-order must guarantee that each number is unique within its specified type.\n* Must prevent the creation of duplicate numbers for the same type.\n* A database-level unique constraint must be implemented to enforce uniqueness.\n\n*4.Storage:*\n\n* Generated numbers must be persistently stored in a database.\n* The database schema must include, at a minimum, the following fields: type, number.\n\n*5.Service-to-Service Communication:*\n\n* The ce-payment service must be able to call the ce-order service's endpoint to retrieve a generated number.\n* The ce-payment service will provide the type parameter when calling the endpoint.\n\nError Handling: Define how the endpoint should handle invalid type values, database errors, or other unexpected issues.\n\n •Number Format: Specify any requirements for the format of the generated numbers (e.g., length, prefix, alphanumeric characters). TBC",
